  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2006-05-03",
    "date": "2006-05-26T19:37:48Z",
    "text": "Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow low and moderate income taxpayers without health insurance a refundable tax credit for 90% of the cost of high deductible health insurance (up to $3,000) to provide coverage for the taxpayer, the taxpayer's spouse, and dependents.\n\n Directs the Secretary of the Treasury to establish a program for making advance payment of tax credit amounts to health insurance providers."
